title._content: First Tree Cutting; Beginning of Construction

description._content: Collection: Stennis Space Center Collection Title: First Tree Cutting; Beginning of Construction Creator: NASA/Stennis Space Center Description: Work crews saw down one of the first trees on May 17, 1963, signaling the beginning of construction of the Mississippi Test Facility in Hancock County, Miss. The tree was cut in Devil's Swamp near the site where the construction dock was built on the turn basin of the man-made canal system. Source: www.archive.org/details/63-021 Identifier: 63-021 Year: 1963 SOURCE: nasaimages.org/luna/servlet/detail/NVA2~37~37~74576~133945 Visit www.nasaimages.org for the most comprehensive compilation of NASA stills, film and video, created in partnership with Internet Archive.
